headline: Mexico’s heavy-truck exports plunges 22% as light-vehicle demand also dips

headline: Cummins (CMI) Valuation Check After 51% Year‑to‑Date Share Price Surge
summary: Cummins (CMI) has quietly powered higher this year, with the stock up about 51% year to date and roughly 28% over the past 3 months. This invites a closer look at what investors might be pricing in. See our latest analysis for Cummins. With the share price now around $523, recent gains have extended a strong run, as investors increasingly price in Cummins’ solid revenue and earnings growth and a stronger long term total shareholder return profile.
